'''Kathy Hoffman''' is an Arizona [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] politician who is the [[Arizona Superintendent of Public Instruction]]-elect, succeeding [[Diane Douglas]] in 2019.

==Education and career==
Hoffman earned a bachelors degree in Japanese Studies at the [[University of Oregon]] in 2009 and a master's degree in speech-language pathology from the [[University of Arizona]] in 2013. She taught pre-school before beginning her career as a speech-language pathologist. Before running for office, Hoffman worked as a speech-language pathologist at Vail Unified School District and Peoria Unified School District.  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/news/political-novice-kathy-hoffman-arizonas-superintendent-10766512|title=Can This 32-Year-Old Teacher Be Arizona's Next Superintendent?|first=Joseph|last=Flaherty|date=30 August 2018|publisher=}}</ref>

Hoffman is fluent in both Japanese and Spanish.

==Superintendent of Public Instruction==
In [[Arizona elections, 2018|2018]], Hoffman defeated former [[Republican party (United States)|Republican]] Congressman [[Frank Riggs]] in the race for [[Superintendent of Public Instruction]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phoenixnewtimes.com/news/kathy-hoffman-wins-race-for-arizona-superintendent-ap-projects-11018329|title=AP: First-Time Candidate Kathy Hoffman Wins Arizona Superintendent Race|first=Joseph|last=Flaherty|date=12 November 2018|publisher=}}</ref> after Hoffman defeated former state senator [[David Schapira]] in the democratic primary in a surprise upset.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://azcapitoltimes.com/news/2018/08/28/arizona-kathy-hoffman-takes-lead-in-schools-chief-democratic-primary/|title=Hoffman victorious in schools chief Democratic primary – Arizona Capitol Times|first=Katie|last=Campbell|website=azcapitoltimes.com}}</ref> She said she was inspired to run after watching the confirmation of [[Betsy DeVos]] as [[United States Secretary of Education|Secretary Education]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/news/politics/elections/2018/10/12/does-kathy-hoffman-have-resume-lead-arizona-schools-frank-riggs-superintendent-public-instruction/1595498002/|title=What experience does a state superintendent need, and does Kathy Hoffman have it?|publisher=}}</ref> Running as a [[clean elections]] candidate, Hoffman managed to out-raise her opponent 2-to-1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/news/politics/elections/2018/10/18/arizona-elections-2018-campaign-finance-reports-show-gop-advantage/1655158002/|title=Republicans have cash edge in expensive campaigns for Arizona's statewide offices|publisher=}}</ref>

