'''Plastro Irrigation Systems Ltd.''' is an [[Israel]]i manufacturer of [[irrigation]] products and a subsidiary of [[Deere & Company]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/feeds/afx/2008/06/05/afx5083423.html|title=Deere buys Plastro to become third largest worldwide in agricultural irrigation|date=2008-06-05|work=Thomson Financial News|accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ishitech.co.il/0708ar4.htm|title=Deere & Company has completed the acquisition of Plastro Irrigation Systems|date=July 2008|work=Israel High-Tech & Investment Report |accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/Ext/Comp/ArticleLayout/CdaArticlePrintPreview/1,2506,L-3424787,00.html|title=John Deere seeking Plastro acquisition|date= 07.12.07|work=Ynet.com|accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref> The company was established in 1966, and today operates through 13 subsidiaries worldwide, with 100 representatives around the world. The company focuses on irrigation solutions within the dynamic irrigation market, on efficient use of water resources and fertilizers to increase yields. Prior to its acquisition by Deere & Company, the company was publicly traded on the [[Tel Aviv Stock Exchange]] where share holders (some through holding entities) included Kibbutz [[Gvat]], [[John Gandel]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-18889064_ITM|title=Gandel to acquire half interest in Kibbutz Gvat plants for NIS 62.5m. |date=February 23, 2005|work=Israel Business Arena via Asia Africa Intelligence Wire|accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref> of Australia and the public.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-21989621_ITM|title=Recanati family invests NIS 6.4m in Plastro Irrigation.|last=Friedman |first=Yaron |date= July 14, 2004|work=Israel Business Arena via Asia Africa Intelligence Wire|accessdate=2009-10-13}}</ref>
Since 2003, Plastro has opened five new commercial and manufacturing subsidiaries in [[Australia]], [[Brazil]], [[Ethiopia]], [[France]] and [[Turkey]].
