'''Robert Kolodner''' is an American [[psychiatrist]] and [[Health informatics|medical informatician]].<ref name=KolodnerActing/> In September 2006, he became the second U.S. [[Office of the National Coordinator for Health Information Technology|National Coordinator for Health IT]].<ref name=KolodnerActing/>
==Career== Kolodner was chief health informatics officer at the [[United States Department of Veterans Affairs|Department of Veterans Affairs]] (VA) and remained on the VA staff while serving as Acting National Coordinator for Health IT.<ref name=KolodnerActing/><ref>{{cite web |last=Ferris |first=Nancy |date=24 January 2007 |title=Kolodner's stint at ONCHIT continues |website=Healthcare IT News |publisher=HIMSS Media |url=http://www.healthcareitnews.com/news/kolodners-stint-onchit-continues |access-date=12 October 2017 }}</ref> [[United States Secretary of Health and Human Services|Health and Human Services Secretary]] [[Mike Leavitt]] officially appointed Kolodner National Coordinator on 18 April 2007.<ref name=Kolodner_permanent/> Kolodner served as National Coordinator until [[David Blumenthal]] assumed the position on 20 April 2009.<ref name=Blumenthal/>
Kolodner retired from the federal government on 23 September 2009.<ref>{{cite web |last=Versel |first=Neil |date=23 September 2009 |title=Kolodner retires from federal government |website=Healthcare IT News |publisher=HIMSS Media |url=http://www.healthcareitnews.com/blog/kolodner-retires-federal-government |access-date=12 October 2017 }}</ref>
